parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor mechanism fails
the seat belt is broken
the front passenger side seatbelt motor fails
the automatic seat belts fail to function properly
the motor does not move back and forth as it should
the upper portion of the seat belt does not hold
the seat belts do not retract every time the door is closed
the seat belt works intermittently
the seat belt gets stuck when getting in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake accumulator switch can cause the power brakes to fail, leading to loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The low fluid indicator light illuminates
the brake pedal becomes hard as a rock
the ABS system fails
and the brakes do not stop the vehicle.

the brakes do not stop the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration in reverse gear can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates while in reverse gear
the accelerator pedal sticks while the car is in reverse
the vehicle takes off unexpectedly while shifting into reverse.
